{
  "stem": "22869.2",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And that's like-- that's like taking away from a human being, today, oxygen.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Because the last thing that was always clinged upon is prayer.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "You know, if you have some straw to hold onto-- to faith, to believe in God, to a prayer-- then somehow, if you're a believer, you think you'll survive.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "There is somebody there, watching over you.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "If they take your prayer book away, and you haven't got that anymore, either, then you're in trouble.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "[DRINKS] But many guys were able, somehow, to-- to hide a psalms or a-- or a prayer book or something and smuggle it in in the camp.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And while we were there the first 24 hours, I remember, I already got a hold of a prayer book, somehow, by miracle.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And-- and the first-- the first impression when we came in-- they didn't detail us to work yet.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "They left us on the bunks after they give us the numbers, and so forth.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "That you had a little time to do or-- whatever you want to.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "So we were visiting with each other and trying to find faces that you knew from home, and so forth.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And we were mostly involved in-- in crying and in praying.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The-- the place itself, the barracks we slept in, were like bunks.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I don't recall whether it was two layers, or two tiers, or three tiers.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I was bunking, at that time, still with my uncle.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And my poor uncle-- my heart broke for him, because I was-- he left a wife at home, with two children, and he had a picture.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He had a prayer book.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And he used to cry there all the time and say prayers.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And it really broke my heart, for him more than for myself.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
